{"title":"Summon Greater Demon","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Summon_Greater_Demon","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.30](/0.30 \"0.30\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n|   |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |\n| - | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | Calls forth one of the greater demons of Pandemonium to serve the caster. With high power, the summoned demon will be less likely to be initially hostile — but the strongest demons may eventually turn against their summoner regardless. |\n\n**Summon Greater Demon** is a monster-only [Summonings](/Summonings \"Summonings\") spell which calls a single [greater demon](/Greater_demon \"Greater demon\") (i.e. tier [1](/1 \"1\") or [2](/2 \"2\")) into existence.\n\nThe following enemies cast Summon Greater Demon:\n\n- e [![Deep elf demonologist.png](/images/5/58/Deep_elf_demonologist.png)](/File:Deep_elf_demonologist.png) **[Deep elf demonologist](/Deep_elf_demonologist \"Deep elf demonologist\")**\n- L [![Dread lich.png](/images/b/bc/Dread_lich.png)](/File:Dread_lich.png) **[Dread lich](/Dread_lich \"Dread lich\")**\n\nThe following enemies may be able to cast Summon Greater Demon, depending on their spell set:\n\n- & [![Pandemonium lord.png](/images/c/c6/Pandemonium_lord.png)](/File:Pandemonium_lord.png) **[Pandemonium lord](/Pandemonium_lord \"Pandemonium lord\")** (8.4% chance)\n\n## History\n\n| [![Summon greater demon.png](/images/e/e1/Summon_greater_demon.png)](/File:Summon_greater_demon.png) Summon Greater Demon |                                                      |\n| :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n| Level                                                                                                                     | 7                                                    |\n| School1                                                                                                                   | [Summoning](/Summonings \"Summonings\")                |\n| Source(s)                                                                                                                 | - [Grand Grimoire](/Grand_Grimoire \"Grand Grimoire\") |\n| [Casting noise](/Spell_noise \"Spell noise\")                                                                               | 6                                                    |\n| [Spell noise](/Spell_noise \"Spell noise\")                                                                                 | 0                                                    |\n\n- Prior to [0.27](/0.27 \"0.27\"), this spell was a Level 7 Summonings spell available to players. For players, Tier 1 demons would eventually turn hostile, while Tier 2 demons had a chance to turn hostile. Also, many of the [Hell](/Hell \"Hell\") lords and unique [pan](/Pan \"Pan\") lords cast Summon Greater Demon instead of a specific, themed summoning spell.\n- Prior to [0.10](/0.10 \"0.10\"), this spell only summoned Tier 1 demons. However, at the time the category included many demons that are now classified as Tier 2, such as balrugs and cacodemons. This meant that every summon would eventually turn hostile.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Summon Greater Demon - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement