4\",\"ttl\":86400,\"transientcontent\":false}}});});</script><script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":183});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"{{version030}}\n{{flavour|Calls forth one of the greater demons of Pandemonium to serve the caster. With high power, the summoned demon will be less likely to be initially hostile — but the strongest demons may eventually turn against their summoner regardless.}}\n\n'''Summon Greater Demon''' is a monster-only [[Summonings]] spell which calls a single [[greater demon]] (i.e. tier [[1]] or [[2]]) into existence. \n\n{{monsters with spell}}\n\n==History==\n{{Spell\n|name=Summon Greater Demon\n|level=7\n|school1={{Summonings}}\n|school2=\n|school3=\n|sources=<div>\n*[[Grand Grimoire]]\n</div>\n|castingnoise=6\n|spellnoise=0\n}}\n*Prior to [[0.27]], this spell was a Level 7 Summonings spell available to players. For players, Tier 1 demons would eventually turn hostile, while Tier 2 demons had a chance to turn hostile. Also, many of the [[Hell]] lords and unique [[pan]] lords cast Summon Greater Demon instead of a specific, themed summoning spell.\n*Prior to [[0.10]], this spell only summoned Tier 1 demons.  However, at the time the category included many demons that are now classified as Tier 2, such as balrugs and cacodemons.  This meant that every summon would eventually turn hostile."}